 * If there exist $i \neq j$ such that $\text{GCD}(nums_i/p, nums_j/p) = 1$, then $\text{GCD}(\{nums_i, nums_j\}) = p$. Since $n \ge 2$, if $n > 2$, $\{i, j\}$ is a proper subset. If $n=2$, $\{i, j\}$ is the whole set.
 * 
