 * 
 * The existence condition is met $\iff$ There is a set of indices $I \subset \{0, \dots, n-1\}$, $I \neq \{0, \dots, n-1\}$, such that $\text{GCD}(\{nums_i | i \in I\}) = p$.
 * 
 * This is true $\iff$ there exists $i \neq j$ such that $\text{GCD}(nums_i, nums_j) = p$, OR
 * $\iff$ there exists $i$ such that $nums_i = p$ AND $n > 1$, OR (if $n=1$ this case is impossible as $n \ge 2$)
 * $\iff$ there exists a subset $I$ of size $\ge 2$ with GCD $p$, OR there exists $i$ such that $nums_i=p$ and $n>1$.
 * 
