 * - If $\exists i \neq j$ such that $\text{GCD}(nums_i, nums_j) = p$, then $\{i, j\}$ is a good subsequence of length 2. YES (since $n \ge 2$, if $n=2$, this is the whole set; if $n>2$, it's proper).
