 * For $n=2$: $\exists i, nums_i=p$.
 * 
 * Since we are updating elements, we must re-evaluate this check efficiently. With $N, Q \approx 5 \cdot 10^4$, $O(Q \cdot N^2)$ is too slow. $O(Q \cdot N)$ is too slow. We need $O(Q \cdot \text{polylog}(N))$.
 * 
