 * 
 * Let $C$ be the set of all GCDs of all pairs $(nums_i, nums_j)$ where $i < j$, plus $\{nums_i\}$ if $nums_i=p$. If $p \in C$, we are good.
 * 
 * Since we have updates, we need a data structure. But GCD is not easily maintained in standard structures.
 * 
 * Given the constraints, the only way this is solvable is if the required property is maintained by a small, easily checkable set of values.
 * 
